RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 84. Maiden Special Weight Purse 45000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLASS CLOWN sped clear quickly, led two wide into the turn then moved to the rail, roused in upper stretch, drew away from SORBET and was in hand nearing the wire. SORBET hopped a bit at the start, chased five deep into the turn, steered to the three path around the bend, closest in pursuit entering the final furlong but was no match for the winner. CON SEAL AND KERRY chased three deep early, took aim three then two wide around the bend but weakened in the stretch run. MOONLIT MISCHIEF chased between foes, had to take up at the seven-sixteenths pole, angled out in the lane and flattened out. BAD CARDINAL chased along the inside to the stretch and faded. SUPER ANNIE chased four wide into the turn, four to five wide into the lane and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Moonlit Mischief
ENTRY.OWNER: Stable Currency LLC and Branham James Doug
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased between, checked 7/16, angled out str, flattened

ENTRY.NAME: Sorbet
ENTRY.COMMENT: hopped bit, chased 5deep, 3wide into str, 2nd best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 96. Claiming Purse 25000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $22,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COLONEL VARGO pressed from outside, fought four wide into the lane, battled head to head with OTRO MAS through the lane and was all to edged the runner-up. OTRO MAS set the pace under pressure from outer rival, led two then three wide around the bend, dueled with the winner through the stretch and finished gamely in defeat. ACQUIRED CLASS chased off the inside then steered out wider early on, chased four wide around the turn, five wide into the stretch, stayed within striking distance into the final furlong and gained late from outside. TOO MUCH INFO settled off the pace, saved ground through the turn, moved out in upper stretch and needed to find more to threaten. STRENGTH OF AUTISM stalked the speed from inside through the turn and weakened in the lane. SAN JAC sat off the pace early on, went two then three wide on the turn and lacked a rally.

ENTRY.NAME: Acquired Class
ENTRY.OWNER: Slam Dunk Racing and SoCal Seven Racing

ENTRY.NAME: Colonel Vargo
ENTRY.OWNER: Rivera Leobardo R and Sosa Manuela Franco
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed outside, 4wide into str, dueled str, all out

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Claiming Purse 29000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DORIE MILLER broke out and brushed rival, stalked the leader up the backstretch, drew alongside approaching the three-eighths pole, quickly took over and clear two then three wide, widened when roused in the lane and was ridden out to the wire. PURA VIDA broke a step slow, chased out of range to the turn, rounded the bend four wide, summoned a mild response and finished a clear second. LOVME LIKEAFOOL chased two wide through the turn, lacked a bid to threaten in the furlong grounds but churned on for the show honors. FIFTY STARS sent clear to establish command, challenged early on the turn, lost command midway around the bend and retreated in the lane. JOSIE EARP hit the gate and got brushed at the start, chased three wide into the turn, dropped back between rivals around the bend, coaxed to the eighth pole then eased in the final furlong and walked off.

ENTRY.NAME: Lovme Likeafool
ENTRY.OWNER: Alvarez Edwin G and Arriaga Dulce

ENTRY.NAME: Dorie Miller
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out/brushed, stalked, cleared turn, ridden out

ENTRY.NAME: Josie Earp
ENTRY.COMMENT: hit gate/brushed, chased off rail, dropped back turn, eased

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 92. Claiming Purse 33000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000.

CLAIM.OWNER: Carney Hugh J and Newport Robert

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLASSYMADEMOISELLE raced up close off the inside, challenged PROFESSORS' PRIDE from outside on the turn, took over at the three-sixteenths pole, put away inner rival past the eighth pole, led clear into the final sixteenth and held late over the runner-up. SHARED FUTURE stalked wide early, angled down to the three path nearing the turn, came four wide into the stretch, rallied in deep stretch but was too late. PROFESSORS' PRIDE set the pace to the turn, challenged by the winner around the bend, maintained a short lead into the stretch, lost command at the three-sixteenths pole, flattened late but managed to save the show. ON PURPOSE stalked from inside, tipped out in upper stretch and missed the show. AMERICAN HEIGHTS got brushed by trouble rival leaving the gate, chased off the rail, asked three wide around the bend and weakened. SUGAR SUGAR hopped and lost the rider at the start and walked off. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INVOLVING THE START OF SUGAR SUGAR AND RULED THAT SHE CAUSED HER OWN PROBLEMS AT THE START AND IS CONSIDERED A STARTER.

ENTRY.NAME: Classymademoiselle
ENTRY.COMMENT: up close, bid outside turn, cleared, held

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Sun Valley Farm & Spendthrift Stallions, LLC

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG CHEDDAR was closest in pursuit of the pacesetter early, drew alongside around the turn, cleared in upper stretch and held well under a drive to the wire. AROUND THE DIAL raced three deep into the turn, ridden along four wide into the drive, loomed entering the final furlong but could not summon the needed late kick. WHOA BUDDY chased four deep at the back entering the turn, came six wide into the lane, chased within striking distance with a furlong remaining but finished evenly late. PERFECTO AMOR tracked the pace from inside, cut the corner into the stretch, moved out a bit in the drive and lacked the needed response. BOOMER JUSTICE stumbled leaving the gate, chased two wide around the bend between rivals and could not rally. DIVINELY DIVERSE stepped to the front and showed the way up the backstretch, set the pace along the inside through the turn, yielded to the winner at the top of the lane and faded out of contention.

ENTRY.NAME: Big Cheddar
ENTRY.COMMENT: up close outside, cleared, held well

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 6 1M Dirt CR: 77. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CONFUCIUS broke out and bumped rival at the start, stalked near the inside then two wide on the first turn, waited for room behind the leaders around the far turn, altered in leaving the bend, reached the front approaching the three-sixteenths pole and edged away to prove best. WHISKEY VISION chased in the two path, moved out on the backstretch, bid four then five wide on the far turn, gained the advantage in upper stretch, relinquished the lead to CONFUCIUS shortly after and stayed on to secure the place. L L L COOL vied between rivals for the lead in the two path to the far turn, fought three wide into the lane and was outfinished in the final furlong. DONTTESTYOURLUCK chased in the four path early, remained wide and came six wide into the lane and lacked a bid. PAT CAN'T COUNT vied three deep to the far turn, four wide into the lane, got crowded between rivals in upper stretch and weakened. NON TOXIC bumped and stumbled leaving the gate, trailed three then four wide early, moved outside rivals in the middle stages, traveled four then five wide at the back on the far turn and was eased in the final furlong. KING HEAT vied for the the lead from inside to the stretch, weakened in the lane, then lugged into the temporary rail approaching the eighth pole, losing the rider in the process and walked off following the race.

ENTRY.NAME: King Heat
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, weakened, lugged in/hit temp rail/lost rider

ENTRY.NAME: Confucius
ENTRY.OWNER: SF Racing LLC Starlight Racing Madaket Stables LLC Masterson Robert E Schoenfarb
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, inside-2wide, waited/altred in 2nd, best late

ENTRY.NAME: Pat Can't Count
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied 3deep, 4wide into str, crowded upper, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 101. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 47000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $40,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 17 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KINGDOM HEART sprinted clear from inside, drifted into the lane, drifted out further in the drive, kept to task in the final furlong and was never challenged. VANCOUGAR stumbled leaving the gate, tracked widest to the turn, went five then six wide around the bend, drifted in and brushed midstretch and outkicked SMUGGLER'S RUN for second. SMUGGLER'S RUN brushed with COOL PAPA G in the beginning, closest three wide into the turn, spun five wide into the drive, got brushed by VANCOUGAR midstretch and was edged by that rival for second. COOL PAPA G brushed with inner rival at the start, chased on the inside into the turn, eased off the rail around the bend and lacked a bid. AMBIVALENT chased two to three wide through the turn and could not rally. JACK SIXPACK broke a step slow, got crowded between rivals early and altered to the inside, saved ground around the bend and failed to menace. RESILIENT chased four wide into the turn, five wide into the lane and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Kingdom Heart
ENTRY.COMMENT: rail speed, drifted into str, never challenged

ENTRY.NAME: Smuggler's Run
ENTRY.OWNER: Rooster Coup Racing and Kagele Tom

ENTRY.NAME: Cool Papa G
ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed start, chased inside, moved out, no bid

ENTRY.NAME: Jack Sixpack
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, crowded early, altered in, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: Vancougar
ENTRY.OWNER: Mark D and Patricia L Cofer Trust and Webb Family Trust

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 8 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 23000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RELAXED ARTIST (IRE) broke in and bumped then lost his path at the start, trailed two wide into the turn, eased out around the bend, closed in steadily through the lane and dug in to get up in the closing moments. THIRSTY veered in at the start, sped clear and showed the way up the backstretch, led a bit off the rail through the turn, drifted into the lane, resisted into the final sixteenth and was nailed at the wire. TANGLEDUPINGREY chased off the rail, bid from outside into the turn, got floated out into the lane, continued to challenge into the final furlong and never could find the needed late kick. HEY BATMAN forwardly placed early on, went two wide around the bend, bid from inside in the final furlong and got outkicked. SPIRITIST got bumped on both sides at the start, chased three wide into the turn, angled six wide, moved out further and put in a mild rally while widest. ABERDEEN'S KNIGHT forwardly placed in the early stages, chased four wide into the drive and flattened. RIPPIN' RUIS (AUS) got bumped in the beginning and crowded shortly after, altered to the inside, saved ground through the turn and failed to menace. HOT MEMORIES tracked in the two path through the turn and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Hot Memories
ENTRY.OWNER: Saratoga West Ortega Jr Alex and Ortega Vincent

ENTRY.NAME: Rippin' Ruis (AUS)
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped/crowded early, saved ground, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: Spiritist
ENTRY.OWNER: Branch William A Jacobs George A and Wallace II Jerry
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, 6wide into str, mild rally

ENTRY.NAME: Thirsty
ENTRY.OWNER: London Tom Lovingier Terry C and Zondlo Eugene
ENTRY.COMMENT: came in start, sped clear, drifted into str, gamely

ENTRY.NAME: Tangledupingrey
ENTRY.OWNER: Han Moon S and Medina Lizbeth
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased off rail, bid outside 7/16, no final kick

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Los Alamitos Special S. LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 9 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 107. Stakes Purse 75000. THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH ARE NON WINNERS OF A SWEEPSTAKES OF *$50,000 AT ONE MILE OR OVER. By Subscription of $100 each to accompany the nomination or by supplementary nomination of $1,500 Due at time of entry. All horses shall pay $250 to pass th e entry box and $250 additional to start, with $75,000 Guaranteed with $45,000 to the winner, $15,000 to Second, $9,000 to Third, $4,500 to Fourth and $1,500 to Fifth. Three year olds 120 lbs. Older 124 lbs. Non winners of $30,000 twice other than maideno r claiming at one mile or over since April 1 allowed 2 lbs. Of such a race of $40,000 in 2022 allowed 4 lbs. High Weights Preferred. Total earnings in 2022 will be used in determining preferences of horses with equal weights. Starters to be named throughh the entry box by closing time of entries. A trophy will be presented to the winner. Nominations close Thursday, September 7, 2023. (If there are less than six (6) Starters, the purse will be reduced to $75,000).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ARHAM rated two to three wide around the clubhouse turn, closest in pursuit up the backstretch, challenged into the far turn, headed IT'S MY HOUSE at the three-eighths pole, inched ahead around the bend, kicked clear in upper stretch and was ridden out in the final furlong. AMERICAN ADMIRAL stalked in the two path outside a rival, went three wide into the far turn, came four wide into the stretch, finished willingly outside SALESMAN (IRE) in the late stages and edged that rival for second. SALESMAN (IRE) broke well then took a stalking position along the inside, ridden along while tipping to the two path on the far turn, moved out in the lane and got outkicked by AMERICAN ADMIRAL for the place honors. IT'S MY HOUSE cleared and crossed over to the inside, showed the way up the backstretch, challenged from outside into the far turn, headed with three furlongs left to run, relinquished the lead soon after and weakened down the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Salesman (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke well, stalked inside-2wide, moved out, edged 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Arham
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated 2-3wide, bid outside 3/8, cleared, ridden out

ENTRY.NAME: It's My House
ENTRY.OWNER: Branch William A Buster Jr William C and Cohen Mark
